    <div id="signals" class="card">
      <h2>Signal Radar</h2>
      <ul class="signal-list">
        <li class="signal-item">
          <span class="signal-icon">🔴</span>
          <div>
            <div class="signal-title">Anthropic: two leaks in one week + Congressional scrutiny</div>
            <div class="signal-desc">Mythos model specs via CMS misconfiguration, Claude Code source via npm packaging error. Rep. Gottheimer questions national security implications.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="signal-item">
          <span class="signal-icon">🔴</span>
          <div>
            <div class="signal-title">Supply chain attacks weaponize security tools</div>
            <div class="signal-desc">TeamPCP compromised Trivy vulnerability scanner, KICS, LiteLLM. The detection-defense loop breaks when scanners become attack vectors. 1,000+ environments affected.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="signal-item">
          <span class="signal-icon">🔴</span>
          <div>
            <div class="signal-title">Axios npm compromise: 100M+ weekly downloads poisoned</div>
            <div class="signal-desc">Credential theft + RAT installation via poisoned versions 1.14.1 and 0.30.4. Dual version strategy targeted both modern and legacy codebases.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="signal-item">
          <span class="signal-icon">🟠</span>
          <div>
            <div class="signal-title">AI agents choose vulnerable dependencies 50% more often</div>
            <div class="signal-desc">Study of 117K dependency changes: AI coding agents systematically favor popularity over security when selecting package versions.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="signal-item">
          <span class="signal-icon">🟠</span>
          <div>
            <div class="signal-title">Oracle 6am email: mass layoff template for AI era</div>
            <div class="signal-desc">30K employees fired simultaneously via email at dawn. No managers, no HR. $8-10B freed for AI data center buildout.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="signal-item">
          <span class="signal-icon">🟠</span>
          <div>
            <div class="signal-title">DMCA overreach: 8,100 repos nuked in 24 hours</div>
            <div class="signal-desc">Anthropic's takedown hit legitimate forks of their own public repo. Retracted, but demonstrates copyright enforcement risk at scale.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="signal-item">
          <span class="signal-icon">🟢</span>
          <div>
            <div class="signal-title">Gemma 4 under Apache 2.0 — Google's open model play</div>
            <div class="signal-desc">31B model ranks #3 globally. Apache 2.0 eliminates legal friction. On-device AI rivaling cloud models from 2025.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="signal-item">
          <span class="signal-icon">🟢</span>
          <div>
            <div class="signal-title">Copilot cloud agent: research → plan → code</div>
            <div class="signal-desc">GitHub's agent now understands codebases, produces implementation plans, executes with signed commits and org governance.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="signal-item">
          <span class="signal-icon">🟢</span>
          <div>
            <div class="signal-title">OpenClaw: agent-as-universal-interface pattern</div>
            <div class="signal-desc">Karpathy's Dobby dynamically discovers and controls arbitrary networked systems. One agent replacing 6+ specialized apps.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="signal-item">
          <span class="signal-icon">🔵</span>
          <div>
            <div class="signal-title">Claude Mythos "Capybara" tier — step-change capabilities</div>
